{
  "stem": "12612.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First, let me say that, as far as we know now, I am the youngest survivor to come out of the concentration camps in the whole Midwest United States.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hitler had some kind of a treaty with England and with Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Being that I was a firstborn child, and I was a British subject, Hitler put us in this holding camp, like a prisoner of war exchange.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the camp was divided in two with a fence.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anne Frank was on the other side.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I found that out later from Anne Frank's girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were on this side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] even though Hitler had the-- the treaty, it didn't stop him from at will just taking people away and-- and killing them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Twice, my brother saved us from the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Once he had a terrible ear infection.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he had a high fever.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were supposed to go on a transport to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the doctor convinced the Nazis that he's untransferable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the doctor was able to give him some morphine to calm him down, so he wouldn't be shot.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was only a year and a half or maybe two at that time already.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the second time, again, they wanted to clean us out and bring us to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my brother had terrible dysentery.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was so bad that the doctor said the only thing that's going to save him is if you beg the old German Jews in the camp in the kitchen to save a little bit of rice water to give to him a teaspoon at a time.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That's the only thing that will save him.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
